{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|1Co|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"For my part, brothers and sisters, I was not able to speak to you as spiritual people but as people of the flesh, as babies in Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"I gave you milk to drink, not solid food, since you were not yet ready for it. In fact, you are still not ready,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"because you are still worldly. For since there is envy and strife among you, are you not worldly and behaving like mere humans?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"For whenever someone says, “I belong to Paul,” and another, “I belong to Apollos,” are you not acting like mere humans?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"What then is Apollos? What is Paul? They are servants through whom you believed, and each has the role the Lord has given.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"I planted, Apollos watered, but God gave the growth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"So, then, neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is anything, but only God who gives the growth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"Now he who plants and he who waters are one, and each will receive his own reward according to his own labor.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"For we are God’s coworkers. You are God’s field, God’s building.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"According to God’s grace that was given to me, I have laid a foundation as a skilled master builder, and another builds on it. But each one is to be careful how he builds on it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":11,"text":"For no one can lay any foundation other than what has been laid down. That foundation is Jesus Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":12,"text":"If anyone builds on the foundation with gold, silver, costly stones, wood, hay, or straw,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":13,"text":"each one’s work will become obvious. For the day will disclose it, because it will be revealed by fire; the fire will test the quality of each one’s work.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":14,"text":"If anyone’s work that he has built survives, he will receive a reward.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":15,"text":"If anyone’s work is burned up, he will experience loss, but he himself will be saved —but only as through fire.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":16,"text":"Don’t you yourselves know that you are God’s temple and that the Spirit of God lives in you?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":17,"text":"If anyone destroys God’s temple, God will destroy him; for God’s temple is holy, and that is what you are.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":18,"text":"Let no one deceive himself. If anyone among you thinks he is wise in this age, let him become a fool so that he can become wise.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":19,"text":"For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God, since it is written, He catches the wise in their craftiness;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":20,"text":"and again, The Lord knows that the reasonings of the wise are futile.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":21,"text":"So let no one boast in human leaders, for everything is yours —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":22,"text":"whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas or the world or life or death or things present or things to come —everything is yours,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","bookOrder":45,"chapter":3,"verse":23,"text":"and you belong to Christ, and Christ belongs to God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Co","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,10,16,18],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Problem of Immaturity"},{"beforeVerse":5,"text":"The Role of God’s Servants"},{"beforeVerse":18,"text":"The Folly of Human Wisdom"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For my part, brothers and sisters, I was not able to speak to you as spiritual people but as people of the flesh, as babies in Christ. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 14:20","book":"1Co","chapter":14,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 5:13","book":"Heb","chapter":5,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 2:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":2,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Co 14:20","book":"1Co","chapter":14,"verse":20},{"label":"Heb 5:13","book":"Heb","chapter":5,"verse":13},{"label":"1Pt 2:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I gave you milk to drink, not solid food, since you were not yet ready for it. In fact, you are still not ready, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"because you are still worldly. For since there is envy "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 3:14","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 3:16","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":16,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and strife "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss add and divisions"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ti 3:9","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":9,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" among you, are you not worldly and behaving like mere humans? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jms 3:14","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":14},{"label":"Jms 3:16","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":16},{"label":"Ti 3:9","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss add and divisions"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For whenever someone says, “I belong to Paul,” and another, “I belong to Apollos,” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ti 3:13","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" are you not acting like mere humans?"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ti 3:13","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"What then is Apollos? What is Paul? They are servants through whom you believed, and each has the role the Lord has given. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I planted, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 18:4–11","book":"Act","chapter":18,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 4:15","book":"1Co","chapter":4,"verse":15,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 9:1","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 15:1","book":"1Co","chapter":15,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" Apollos watered, but God gave the growth. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 18:4–11","book":"Act","chapter":18,"verse":4},{"label":"1Co 4:15","book":"1Co","chapter":4,"verse":15},{"label":"1Co 9:1","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":1},{"label":"1Co 15:1","book":"1Co","chapter":15,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So, then, neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is anything, but only God who gives the growth. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now he who plants and he who waters are one, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or of equal status, or united in purpose"},{"kind":"text","text":" and each will receive his own reward according to his own labor. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or of equal status, or united in purpose"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For we are God’s coworkers. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Or are coworkers belonging to God"},{"kind":"text","text":" You are God’s field, God’s building. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 2:5","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":5,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Pt 2:5","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Or are coworkers belonging to God"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"According to God’s grace that was given to me, I have laid a foundation as a skilled master builder, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or wise master builder"},{"kind":"text","text":" and another builds on it. But each one is to be careful how he builds on it. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or wise master builder"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For no one can lay any foundation "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 28:16","book":"Isa","chapter":28,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 15:20","book":"Rom","chapter":15,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 10:16","book":"2Co","chapter":10,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 11:4","book":"2Co","chapter":11,"verse":4,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 1:6–9","book":"Gal","chapter":1,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" other than what has been laid down. That foundation is Jesus Christ. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 28:16","book":"Isa","chapter":28,"verse":16},{"label":"Rm 15:20","book":"Rom","chapter":15,"verse":20},{"label":"2Co 10:16","book":"2Co","chapter":10,"verse":16},{"label":"2Co 11:4","book":"2Co","chapter":11,"verse":4},{"label":"Gl 1:6–9","book":"Gal","chapter":1,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"If anyone builds on the foundation with gold, silver, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 5:3","book":"Jas","chapter":5,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" costly stones, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 17:4","book":"Rev","chapter":17,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" wood, hay, or straw, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jms 5:3","book":"Jas","chapter":5,"verse":3},{"label":"Rv 17:4","book":"Rev","chapter":17,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Co:3:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"each one’s work will become obvious. For the day will disclose it, because it will be revealed by fire; "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Th 1:8","book":"2Th","chapter":1,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 1:7","book":"1Pe","chapter":1,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" the fire will test the quality of each one’s work. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 62:12","book":"Psa","chapter":62,"verse":12,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 24:12","book":"Pro","chapter":24,"verse":12,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 16:27","book":"Mat","chapter":16,"verse":27,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 5:10","book":"2Co","chapter":5,"verse":10,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 1:17","book":"1Pe","chapter":1,"verse":17,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Th 1:8","book":"2T